width="1125" height="844" alt="Responding to workplace burnout: A guide for leaders - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" title="Responding to workplace burnout: A guide for leaders - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-leSONj uTJGF pf-15_"/></div></div></div></div></div><div data-section-id="pf-895a" data-category="Generic Content" data-name="Matcha" data-pf-type="Section" class="sc-jefHZX ePVSNw pf-16_"><div style="--cw:1170px" class="sc-ihINtW iHyUfe"><div class="sc-iAKWXU lesjfG pf-17_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:0px;--s-sm:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-bXdNzS hYBROi pf-18_"><p class="sc-dYtuZ JoqQF pf-19_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-eTwdGJ utmwk pf-21_">As managers and business leaders, how do you support employees when they feel burnt out? Can you identify the signs of burnout in the workplace? Do you have structures in place to deal with workplace burnout? Where to look for guidance and tools to deal with workplace burnout?<br><br>In this article, <a href="https://www.mandatorytraining.co.uk/pages/dr-richard-dune-blog" target="_blank"><i><span style="color: rgb(0, 102, 204);">Dr Richard Dune</span></i></a> guides managers and leaders on how to respond to employee burnout.</span></p><h2 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-jeraig eTNnJl pf-22_ _Y6RW61"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-eTwdGJ utmwk pf-24_">Dealing with employee burnout 
</span></h2><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Dealing_with_employee_burnout_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.png?v=1692177314" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Dealing_with_employee_burnout_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.png?v=1692177314 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Dealing_with_employee_burnout_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_500x.png?v=1692177314 320w" width="1536" height="864" alt="Dealing with employee burnout - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" title="Dealing with employee burnout - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-leSONj uTJGF pf-25_"/><p class="sc-dYtuZ JoqQF pf-26_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-eTwdGJ utmwk pf-28_">Burnout has become an increasingly common problem in today's workplaces, putting employees' well-being and organisational performance at risk. As a manager or entrepreneur, it's essential to recognise the signs of burnout and respond in a supportive and constructive way when an employee reports it.<br><br>In a recent article for Harvard Business Review, Noemie Le Pertel provided some practical tips for responding when an employee tells you they're burned out. In this blog, we'll go through those tips and provide additional recommendations for preventing and addressing burnout in the workplace.</span></p><h2 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-jeraig eTNnJl pf-29_ _Y6RW61"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-eTwdGJ utmwk pf-31_">Listen actively and empathetically
</span></h2><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Listen_actively_and_empathetically_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.png?v=1692177400" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Listen_actively_and_empathetically_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.png?v=1692177400 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Listen_actively_and_empathetically_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_500x.png?v=1692177400 320w" width="1368" height="912" alt="Listen actively and empathetically - Responding to workplace burnout - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" title="Listen actively and empathetically - Responding to workplace burnout - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-leSONj uTJGF pf-32_"/><p class="sc-dYtuZ JoqQF pf-33_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-eTwdGJ utmwk pf-35_">When an employee tells you they are burned out, scheduling a one-on-one meeting and setting aside dedicated time to listen to them is vital. It's crucial to let them fully express their thoughts without interrupting and to practice active listening by repeating what you've heard and asking for clarification when needed.<br><br>Show empathy by validating their feelings and letting them know you care about their well-being.</span></p><h2 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-jeraig eTNnJl pf-36_ _Y6RW61"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-eTwdGJ utmwk pf-38_">Identify the root causes
</span></h2><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Identify_the_root_causes_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.png?v=1692177473" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Identify_the_root_causes_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.png?v=1692177473 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Identify_the_root_causes_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_500x.png?v=1692177473 320w" width="1471" height="981" alt="Identify the root causes of workplace burnout - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" title="Identify the root causes of workplace burnout - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-leSONj uTJGF pf-39_"/><p class="sc-dYtuZ JoqQF pf-40_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-eTwdGJ utmwk pf-42_">Understanding what's causing employee burnout is necessary to address the issue effectively. Ask open-ended questions about their stressors and other factors contributing to their burnout. Some common root causes include high workload, insufficient resources or support, lack of autonomy or control, and feeling undervalued or under-compensated. Use this information to tailor solutions and address the underlying issues.</span></p><h2 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-jeraig eTNnJl pf-43_ _Y6RW61"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-eTwdGJ utmwk pf-45_">Develop a plan to support employee well-being
</span></h2><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Develop_a_plan_to_support_employee_well-being_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.png?v=1692177554" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Develop_a_plan_to_support_employee_well-being_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.png?v=1692177554 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Develop_a_plan_to_support_employee_well-being_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_500x.png?v=1692177554 320w" width="1260" height="840" alt="Develop a plan to support employee well-being - Responding to employee burnout - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" title="Develop a plan to support employee well-being - Responding to employee burnout - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-leSONj uTJGF pf-46_"/><p class="sc-bvFjSx yVjXo pf-47_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Once you've gathered information about the causes of employee burnout, it's time to develop a plan to support them. Some short-term strategies include flexible scheduling, providing resources or support, and giving extra time off. Long-term strategies can include regular check-ins, problem-solving and feedback sessions, career development opportunities, stress management training, and wellness initiatives. Ensure the plan is sustainable and feasible, and monitor the employee's burnout.<br> 
</p><h2 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-jeraig eTNnJl pf-49_ _Y6RW61"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-eTwdGJ utmwk pf-51_">Preventing burnout
</span></h2><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Preventing_burnout_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.png?v=1692177610" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Preventing_burnout_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.png?v=1692177610 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Preventing_burnout_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_500x.png?v=1692177610 320w" width="1843" height="1067" alt="Preventing burnout - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" title="Preventing burnout - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-leSONj uTJGF pf-52_"/><p class="sc-bvFjSx yVjXo pf-53_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">As a manager, you can take proactive measures to prevent burnout in the workplace. Encourage breaks and prioritise work-life balance. Offer support and resources, such as mentoring and training programs, to help employees manage their workload better. Provide feedback and recognition to employees to feel valued and motivated.<br> 
