</p><ul style="--text-indent:0;--line-spacing:10px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-aaqME bBWRSi pf-74_"><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-iRFsWr jqRXMU pf-75_">Schedule regular check-ins to track employee burnout and provide regular feedback and support.</li><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-iRFsWr jqRXMU pf-77_">Encourage work-life balance and offer resources such as mentoring or training programs to help manage workload better.</li></ul><h2 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-jeraig eTNnJl pf-79_ _Y6RW61"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-eTwdGJ utmwk pf-81_">Conclusion</span></h2><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Responding_to_workplace_burnout_A_guide_for_leaders_-_Conclusion_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.png?v=1692177953" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Responding_to_workplace_burnout_A_guide_for_leaders_-_Conclusion_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.png?v=1692177953 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Responding_to_workplace_burnout_A_guide_for_leaders_-_Conclusion_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_500x.png?v=1692177953 320w" width="1663" height="1122" alt="Responding to workplace burnout: A guide for leaders - Conclusion - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" title="Responding to workplace burnout: A guide for leaders - Conclusion - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-leSONj uTJGF pf-82_"/><p class="sc-bvFjSx yVjXo pf-83_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Burnout can harm an employee's well-being, the team's morale, and the organisation's performance. It's imperative to take proactive measures to prevent burnout and support employees to avoid experiencing it.<br><br>As a manager or entrepreneur, listening actively and empathetically, identifying the root causes of burnout, and developing feasible support plans can ensure a healthy work environment with en